title: Setting aarch64-apple-darwin as default toolchain on M1 breaks compilation
body:
<!--
Thank you for filing a bug report! 🐛 Please provide a short summary of the bug,
along with any information you feel relevant to replicating the bug.
-->

Installing via `rustup` and setting `aarch64-apple-darwin` as the default toolchain by opting for a custom installation seems to break any attempts at compiling any Rust project, even a brand new `cargo new`. 

Running `rustup show` outputs
```
Default host: aarch64-apple-darwin
rustup home:  /Users/seanchen/.rustup

nightly-aarch64-apple-darwin (default)
rustc 1.52.0-nightly (a143517d4 2021-02-16)
```

When attempting to compile any project via `cargo`, I get 
